  "text": "• Transverse myelitis: Sensory impairment and paresthesia in the extremities are two common presentations of acute transverse myelitis [CITATION_1] (55) [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . That is a relatively uncommon neurological disease in which affected patients exhibit acute dehabilitating symptoms associated with the loss of spinal cord segment function.",
